#week-title("Three", "The Three Stages of a Vigil")

=== Core Teaching

Every vigil progresses through three distinct stages of perception:

1.  *Settling:* The first phase, where the mind is still active with daily
    concerns. The practitioner simply sits and lets the inner noise subside.
2.  *Attending:* The second phase, where attention becomes focused and steady.
    The details of the plant — its movement, its color, its environment — become
    the primary objects of awareness.
3.  *Receiving:* The final phase, where the distinction between observer and
    observed begins to soften. The "felt sense" of the plant's character — its
    Sulphur, its nature — becomes available to direct perception.

=== Topics This Week

- Navigating the three stages of perception
- Receptive attention vs. active projection
- Identifying the "felt sense" of a living signature

#inner-work[
  *The Second Formal Vigil*

  Conduct your second formal vigil this month, this time with a plant you *do not*
  yet know.

  *The Practice:*
  Apply the same protocol as Week 2. Observe. Do not try to "name" the plant or
  categorise it intellectually. Simply receive its presence. Record your notes
  immediately after the session. Compare the "felt sense" of this unknown plant
  with your original one.
]

